Pancake is a fast, simple and lightweight HTTP-Server written in PHP with acceleration for PHP-powered websites.

System requirements:

POSIX-compliant operating system (should run fine on Linux, BSD, Apple Mac OS X, etc. but won't run under any version of Microsoft Windows)
PHP 5.3.0 or newer compiled with --enable-pcntl, --enable-sysvshm and --enable-sysvmsg (PHP 5.4 recommended!)
PECL yaml 1.1.0 or newer
DeepTrace 1.3.0 or newer (DeepTrace is delivered with Pancake but the currently bundled version is outdated, so will have to compile it yourself)

Installing Pancake:

1. cd /usr/local/
2. git clone git://github.com/pp3345/Pancake/
3. cd Pancake/conf
4. cp config.example.yml config.yml
5. Configure a vHost (example in Pancake/conf/vhosts/example.yml)

Running Pancake:

/usr/local/Pancake/sys/pancake.sh

(as root, you may use sudo)

Compiling DeepTrace:

1. cd
2. git clone git://github.com/NeoXiD/DeepTrace
3. cd DeepTrace
4. phpize
5. ./configure
6. make
7. cp modules/DeepTrace.so /usr/local/Pancake/sys/ext/<arch>_<phpver>.so (for example x86_64_54.so for x86_64 and PHP 5.4)

